# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:
# - feat: A new feature (MINOR version bump)
# - fix: A bug fix (PATCH version bump)
# - security: Security vulnerability fix (PATCH version bump)
# - perf: Performance improvement (PATCH version bump)
# - docs: Documentation only changes (no version bump)
# - style: Code style changes (formatting, etc.) (no version bump)
# - refactor: Code refactoring (no version bump)
# - test: Adding or updating tests (no version bump)
# - chore: Maintenance tasks (no version bump)
# - build: Build system changes (no version bump)
# - ci: CI/CD changes (no version bump)
#
# Scope is optional and can be anything specifying the place of the commit change.
# Examples: api, ui, auth, device, docker, deps
#
# Subject should be a short, imperative description of the change.
#
# Body should include the motivation for the change and contrast with previous behavior.
#
# Footer should contain any information about Breaking Changes and is also the place
# to reference GitHub issues that this commit closes.
#
# Breaking Changes should start with "BREAKING CHANGE:" (triggers MAJOR version bump)
#
# Example:
# --------
# feat(api): add device grouping endpoint
#
# Implement new REST API endpoint for managing device groups.
# This allows users to organize devices into logical groups
# for better management and bulk operations.
#
# Closes #123